msgid ""
"\n"
"              Kia ora,<br/>\n"
"              Through the use of this portal, we collect personal "
"information from you, including information about your:\n"
"              <ul>\n"
"                <li>name</li>\n"
"                <li>contact information, such as your email</li>\n"
"                <li>career and education history</li>\n"
"                <li>demographic information, such as your gender and "
"ethnicity</li>\n"
"                <li>your ORCID iD and other research identifiers that you "
"choose</li>\n"
"              </ul>\n"
"              <p>We collect your personal information in order to be able to "
"administer selection and award processes.<br/>\n"
"              We collect demographic data in order to understand the nature "
"of the research community and test ourselves\n"
"              for potential biases in both participation and selection.<br/"
">\n"
"              We collect research identifiers to allow you to reuse "
"information from your ORCID record to assist in creating\n"
"              your portal profile, and to supplement CV information where "
"available.<br/>\n"
"              <p>If you are successful in an application for an award, prize "
"or contract, your name and current\n"
"              place of education/employment will be made public.</p>\n"
"              <p>Besides our staff at Royal Society Te Apārangi, we will "
"share information with the Ministry of Business, Innovation\n"
"              and Employment via the New Zealand Research Information System "
"(NZRIS) in order to meet our obligations for administering\n"
"              these programmes; what is shared and the use permitted within "
"NZRIS is under your control using the Protection\n"
"              Pattern section of your portal profile.</p>\n"
"              <p>Providing some information to this portal is optional.<br/"
">\n"
"              If you choose not to enter contact and career information, we "
"may be unable to process Prize applications that involve your participation."
"<br/>\n"
"              If you choose not to enter demographic information, we will "
"have less information about our support for the New Zealand research "
"sector,\n"
"              but this will have no effect on the assessment of Prizes that "
"you are involved with.</p>\n"
"              <p>We keep your information safe by following current best "
"practice for use of cloud services.</p>\n"
"              You have the right to ask for a copy of any personal "
"information we hold about you, and to ask for it to be corrected if you "
"think it is wrong.<br/>\n"
"              Please contact privacy.officer@royalsociety.org.nz if you "
"would like to exercise these rights.\n"
"            "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"              Kia ora,<br>\n"
"              Mā te whakamahi i tēnei tomokanga, ka kohi mātou i ngā "
"mōhiohio whaiaro i a koe, tae atu ki ngā mōhiohio mō tō:\n"
"              <ul>\n"
"                <li>ingoa</li>\n"
"                <li>mōhiohio whakapā, pērā i to īmēra</li>\n"
"                <li>whakaraupapatanga umanga me te mātauranga</li>\n"
"                <li>mōhiohio hangapori, pērā i tō ira me tō mātāwaka</li>\n"
"                <li>tō ORCID iD me ētahi atu tautohu ranghau ka kōwhiria e "
"koe</li>\n"
"              </ul>\n"
"              <p>Ka kohi mātou i ō mōhiohio whaiaro kia āhei ai ki te "
"whakahaere i ngā pūnaha whiri me te whakawhiwhi i ngā Paraihe<br>\n"
"              Ka kohi mātou i ngā raraunga hangapori kia mōhio ai ki te āhua "
"o te hāpori rangahau me te whakamātau i a mātou anō mō ngā mariu i roto pea "
"i te whakaurunga me te whiringa o ngā Paraihe.<br>\n"
"              Ka kohi mātou i ngā tautohunga rangahau kia āhei koe ki te "
"whakamahi anō i ngā mōhiohio o tō pūkete ORCID i te waihangatanga o tō kāhua "
"i roto i tēnei tomokanga, me te tautoko i ngā mōhiohio tātai pūmanawa ina e "
"āhei ana.<br>\n"
"              <p>Mēnā he kaiwhiwhi koe i tētahi Paraihe, ka hora tō ingoa me "
"tō wāhi ako/mahi o nāianei ki te hunga tūmatanui.</p>\n"
"              <p>Atu i a mātou kaimahi, ka tuaritia he mōhiohio ki  te "
"Pūnaha Mōhiohio Rangahau o Aotearoa (NZRIS) kia tutuki ai i ā mātou "
"takohanga mō te whakahaere i ngā Paraihe; kei a koe te tikanga mēnā ka "
"tuaritia ka whakamahia hoki ngā mōhiohio ki roto i a NZRIS mā te whakamahi i "
"te wāhanga Tauira Parahau o tō kāhua tomokanga.</p>\n"
"              <p>Kei a koe te tikanga mēnā ka tuku i ētahi mōhiohio ki tēnei "
"tomokanga.<br>\n"
"              Ki te kore koe e tāuru i ngā mōhiohio whakapā, umanga mahi "
"hoki, ka kore pea mātou e tukatuka i ngā tono Paraihe e whai wāhi atu ai koe."
"<br/>\n"
"              Ki te kore koe e tāuru i ngā mōhiohio hangapori, ka kore e "
"rahi ngā mōhiohio mō tā mātou tautoko i te wāhanga rangahau o Aotearoa, "
"engari kāore tēnei e pā ki te aromatawai o ngā Paraihe e whai wāhi atu ai "
"koe.</p>\n"
"              <p>Ka noho haumaru ō mōhiohio mā te whai i ngā tino tikanga mō "
"ngā ratonga kapua o nāianei.</p>\n"
"              Kei a koe te tikanga ki te tono atu mō tētahi tārua o ngā "
"mōhiohio whaiaro e pupuri nei e mātou mōu, me te tono kia whakatikahia mēnā "
"ki tō whakaaro kei te hē.<br/>\n"
"              Tēnā whakapā atu ki privacy.officer@royalsociety.org.nz ki te "
"hiahia koe ki te pēnei.\n"
"            "

#: portal/templates/profile_protection_patterns.html:18
msgid ""
"\n"
"    Protection Pattern settings are used by us to determine what we can and "
"can't share about you.<br>\n"
"    Note these options come from the New Zealand Research Information System "
"(NZRIS) and control how, and whether, your data will appear in NZRIS.<br>\n"
"    Each option has tooltips to explain what they control.  If you wish any "
"protection to expire, please state when protection can be removed.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"<p>Ko ngā tautuhinga Tauira Whakamaru ka whakamahia e mātau hei whakatau i "
"ngā mea ka taea te tuari mōu mē ngā mea kāore e pai. </p><p>Ko ngā "
"tautuhinga Tauira Whakamaru ka Me mōhio koe i ahu mai ēnei kōwhiringa mai i "
"te Pūnaha Mōhiohio Rangahau o Aotearoa (NZRIS), me pēhea te whakahaere, ā, "
"ka pēhea te whakaatu i ō raraunga ki te NZRIS. </p><p>He aki utauta tō ia "
"kōwhiringa hei whakamārama i ngā mea kei te whakahaerehia. Mēnā e hiahia ana "
"koe kia mōnehu he whakamarutanga, me tuhi mō āhea tango ai i te "
"whakamarutanga. </p>\n"
"  "

