#: portal/templates/profile_section.html:17
msgid ""
"\n"
"        Organisations that you have an affiliation with.\n"
"        Note that the organisation where you are primarily employed, or "
"study, will be published if you are awarded a prize.\n"
"      "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"          Ngā whakahaere e whai pānga ana koe.\n"
"          Kia mōhio koe, ko te whakahaere e tino mahi ana koe, e ako ana "
"rānei, ka whakaputaina mēnā ka whakawhiwhia koe ki tētahi paraihe.\n"
"        "

#: portal/templates/profile_section.html:22
msgid ""
"\n"
"        Career stage is requested to be able to understand the proportion of "
"researchers at different stages of their career.\n"
"        The expectation is that this will assist in the development of "
"funding mechanisms and support tools.\n"
"        Only used at aggregated levels for statistical and reporting "
"purposes.\n"
"      "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"        E tonoa ana he raupapa ara mahi kia mārama ai ki te ōwehenga o ngā "
"kairangahau i te wāhanga rerekē o tōna ara mahi rerekē.\n"
"Ko te manako ka āwhina tēnei ki te hanga tikanga tuku pūtea me ngā utauta "
"tautoko.\n"
"Ka whakamahia anake i ngā taumata tōpū mō ngā kaupapa tatauranga me te tuku "
"pūrongo.\n"
"        "

#: portal/templates/profile_section.html:28
msgid ""
"\n"
"        Identifiers that are yours in public systems, e.g. authenticated "
"ORCID iD, Scopus ID, ResearcherID, and Teacher Registration Number.\n"
"        Please DO NOT enter personal identifiers such as IRD Number, "
"National Student Number or National Health Number.\n"
"      "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"        Ko ō pūtautuhi i roto i ngā pūnaha tūmatanui, hei tauira, ORCID ID "
"kua whakatūturutia, ID Kairangahau, me te Tau Rēhita Kaiako. KAUA e tāuru "
"pūtautuhi whaiaro pērā i te Tau IRD, Tau Ākonga ā-Motu, Tau Hauora ā-Motu "
"rānei.\n"
"        "

#: portal/templates/profile_section.html:33
msgid ""
"\n"
"        Curriculum Vitae are required from the following:\n"
"        <ul>\n"
"          <li>Team leaders and sole applicants with the exception of the "
"Future Scientist Prize.\n"
"            Applicants for the Future Scientist Prize DO NOT need to provide "
"a CV.</li>\n"
"          <li>Nominators for the Science Teacher Prize</li>\n"
"          <li>Referees for all prizes with the exception of the Future "
"Scientist and Science Teacher Prizes</li>\n"
"        </ul>\n"
"        If in doubt skip this step, and when required a CV will be requested."
"<br><br>\n"
"        For NZ-based researchers, a current CV in the\n"
"        <a href=\"https://www.royalsociety.org.nz/assets/documents/NZ-RST-CV-"
"Template.doc\">NZ RST CV Template</a> is preferred.\n"
"        All others, please provide a CV in whatever is your preferred "
"format.\n"
"      "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"       <p>E hiahiatia ana he Tāhuhu Tangata mai i ēnei e whai ake:</p>\n"
"        <ul>\n"
"          <li>Ngā kaiārahi rōpū me ngā kaitono takitahi, hāunga te Tohu "
"Tohunga Pūtaiao Anamata. KĀORE E MATE ngā kaitono mō te Tohu Tohunga Pūtaiao "
"Anamata ki te tuku tētahi tāhuhu tangata.</li>\n"
"          <li>Ngā kaikōhari mō te Tohu Kaiako Pūtaiao.</li>\n"
"          <li>Ngā kaitautoko mō ngā paraihe katoa, hāunga Ngā Tohu Tohunga "
"Anamata me te Kaiako Pūtaiao.</li>\n"
"        </ul>\n"
"<p>Mēnā kei te māharahara waiho tēnei wāhanga, ā, ina hiahiatia ana ka tonoa "
"he tāhuhu tangata.</p>\n"
"<p>Mō ngā kairangahau kei Aotearoa, he pai ake tētahi tāhuhu tangata "
"onāianei i roto i te <a href=\"https://www.royalsociety.org.nz/assets/"
"documents/NZ-RST-CV-Template.doc\">Tauira Tāhuhu Tangata NZ RST CV.</a> Mō "
"ētahi atu, me tuku mai he tāhuhu tangata ki te takotoranga e hiahia ana koe. "
"He 2 whārangi te mōrahi.\n"
"</p>\n"
"        "

#: portal/templates/profile_section.html:47
msgid ""
"\n"
"        Academic record is requested to enable analysis of the effect of "
"qualifications on research performance,\n"
"        career trajectories, and to better understand needs for succession "
"planning and support for particular groups.\n"
"      "
